  "prompt": "How can I reset password of Instagram account without email?",
  "response": "If you need to reset your Instagram password but don't have access to your email, you can try the following methods:\n\n1. **Using Your Phone Number:**\n   - Open the Instagram app or website.\n   - Click on \"Forgot password?\".\n   - Enter your username or phone number associated with your account.\n   - Follow the prompts to receive a password reset link via SMS.\n\n2. **Facebook Account:**\n   - If your Instagram account is linked to your Facebook account, you can reset your password by logging in through Facebook.\n   - On the login screen, click on \"Log in with Facebook\" and follow the prompts.\n\n3. **Trusted Contacts or Recovery Codes:**\n   - If you set up two-factor authentication or trusted contacts, you can follow the instructions provided during the setup to regain access to your account.\n\n4. **Contact Instagram Support:**\n   - If none of the above options work, you can try reaching out to Instagram Support for help. You may need to provide verification information to prove your identity.\n\nMake sure to keep your account recovery options up-to-date in the future to avoid similar issues.",
